@node important "ListServ 1.0b2 Important Information"

ListServ and its documentation are currently in BETA. This means that it is
currently being tested, and this is a test version of it. ListServ (and its
documentation) are in no way complete, and no gurantees are made as to its
functionality or features. 

This is the second public beta release of ListServ. ListServ is being
developed as an open beta application. That means that there are no private
betas. The only person that gets to see bits in between public releases is me.

Users of the first beta release MUST MUST MUST MUST MUST MUST MUST MUST MUST
read the readme. This is EXTREMELY IMPORTANT. If you dont read it, then you
have only YOURSELF to blame for messing up your ENTIRE mailing lists. Have i
made myself clear ? No ? Well here it is again in bold underlined italics just
in case :)

@{b}@{i}@{u}Users of the first beta release MUST MUST MUST MUST MUST MUST MUST MUST MUST
read the readme. This is EXTREMELY IMPORTANT. If you dont read it, then you
have only YOURSELF to blame for messing up your ENTIRE mailing lists. Have i
made myself clear ? Good.@{ub}@{ui}@{uu}

@endnode

@node intro "Introduction to ListServ"

ListServ allows you to run mailing lists on your Amiga. This is not limited
to the internet only, it can be setup for local networks and with a little
work a FidoNet style mail network. There is no need for a 24 hour connection,
although your lists will be considerably faster if you are connected 24 hours.
ListServ supports many powerfull features, it tries to combine all the
features you would need in a list server and makes everything totally
optional. You run the lists the way _you_ want to, not the way the programmer
does. Also, its possible to have more then one list and each list with its
own settings, for instance, you may want a discussion list for posting from
anyone, and another list as announce, for posts only by you and the list
owner. You may want the announce list to have a digest, and the discussion
list not to, all of this is possible with ListServ, and more.

BETA NOTE: This beta version does not support announce lists, digests and a
few other things mentioned above.
@endnode

